Certainly! You can loop through the array in JavaScript using various methods. One of the most common methods is using a `for` loop. Here's how you can loop through the `myArr` array and print each value:

```javascript
const myArr = ["mango", "apple", "strawberry", "orange", "watermelon"];

for (let i = 0; i < myArr.length; i++) {
  console.log(myArr[i]);
}
```

In this loop, `i` starts at 0 (the index of the first element in the array) and goes up to the length of the array minus 1 (since array indices are zero-based). `myArr[i]` represents each element of the array as the loop iterates, and `console.log()` is used to print each value to the console.
